JavaScript Day 4 – Loops ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Loops allow you to repeat a block of code multiple times without writing it repeatedly.

Instead of this:

console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");

You can simply write:

for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    console.log("Hello");
}
Types of Loops

Today we'll learn:

for
while
do...while
for...of
for...in
break
continue
1. for Loop ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

The for loop is the most commonly used loop in JavaScript.

Syntax
for (initialization; condition; increment/decrement) {
    // Code to execute
}
Example
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    console.log(i);
}
Output
1
2
3
4
5
How the for loop works
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    console.log(i);
}
Step-by-step
Step	Value of i	Condition	Output
Start	1	1 <= 5 ✅	1
Next	2	2 <= 5 ✅	2
Next	3	3 <= 5 ✅	3
Next	4	4 <= 5 ✅	4
Next	5	5 <= 5 ✅	5
Next	6	6 <= 5 ❌	Stop
